==Career== Coming through the youth ranks at Crystal Palace, he signed his first professional contract in December 2015. On 10 September 2017, he made his debut as a [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] in the [[Premier League]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Parry|first=Richard|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/burnley-1-crystal-palace-0-frank-de-boer-s-job-on-the-line-as-chris-wood-goal-inflicts-fourth-a3631276.html|title=De Boer’s job on the line as Palace lose again|work=Evening Standard|location=London|date=10 September 2017|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref>
On 31 August 2018, Lumeka signed for [[National League (English football)|National League]] side [[Leyton Orient F.C.|Leyton Orient]] on loan until the end of the 2018–19 season.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lumeka Joins Leyton Orient on Loan|url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/2018/august/lumeka-joins-leyton-orient-on-loan/|website=cpfc.co.uk|date=1 September 2018|accessdate=1 September 2018}}</ref> He was recalled from the loan on 9 January 2019 having made only one appearance for Orient.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/levi-lumeka-returns-to-palace-from-orient-loan-spell/|title=Levi Lumeka Recalled From Leyton Orient Loan Spell|website=cpfc.co.uk|language=en-gb|date=9 January 2019|access-date=9 January 2019}}</ref>
